12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5013.4 of Title 74, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
17 fund for the Oklahoma Department of Commerce to be designated the
18 “Olympics in Oklahoma Revolving Fund”. The fund shall be a
19 continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall
20 consist of all monies received by the Department from
21 appropriations, donations, grants, and other sources of funding for
22 the purpose of hosting the 2028 Olympic Games. Expenditures from
23 the fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer
24 against claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1378 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 Offi ce of Management and Enterprise Services for approval and
2 payment.
3 B. Subject to approval by the Oklahoma Department of Commerce,
4 no less than five percent (5%) of all funds dispensed from the fund
5 shall be awarded to contracts fulfilled by Oklahoma-based
6 businesses.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
8 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
9 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
10 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
11 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
12 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON APPROPRIATIONS
